@startuml
autonumber
actor "Prosumer" as P

box "Orchestration Layer" #LightCyan
participant "Camunda Engine" as Camunda
participant "Kong Gateway" as Kong
end box

box "Microservice Layer" #LightYellow
participant "AssetLink MS" as ALMS
participant "Telemetry MS" as TMS
end box

box "Infrastructure Layer" #LightGreen
database "AWS RDS" as DB
queue "Kafka Cluster" as Kafka
end box

== Asset Link Provisioning / Decommissioning ==

note over P, Kafka: For Decommissioning, the same steps are conceptually executed in reverse: The Telemetry Consumer thread is stopped,\nthe Kafka Topic is deleted, and finally the AssetLink is removed from RDS via DELETE /AssetLink/{id}.

P -> Camunda: Trigger AssetLink\nManagement Process\n(Onboard/Offboard)

Camunda -> Kong: POST /AssetLink\n{idProsumer, idUtilityOperator}
Kong -> ALMS: Forward Request

ALMS -> DB: JDBC INSERT INTO AssetLink\n(idProsumer, idUtilityOperator)
DB --> ALMS: Return Generated ID (AssetLinkID)

ALMS --> Kong: 201 Created\nURI: /AssetLink/{AssetLinkID}
Kong --> Camunda: 201 Created

Camunda -> Kafka: Create Topic\n'{AssetLinkID}-{idUtilityOperator}'
Kafka --> Camunda: Ack

Camunda -> Kong: POST /Telemetry/Consume\nTopicName: '{AssetLinkID}-{idUtilityOperator}'
Kong -> TMS: Forward Request

TMS -> Kafka:Dynamic Topic Consumer\nThread Subscribe to Topic \n'{AssetLinkID}-{idUtilityOperator}'
Kafka --> TMS: Ack

TMS --> Kong: 200 OK ("New worker started")
Kong --> Camunda: Consumer State Updated

Camunda --> P: Asset Link\nProvisioned or\nDecommissioned
@enduml